Rating: 4
I was looking for a recipe for Jack Daniels Pecan Pie, but all I could find were recipes containing corn syrup -- yuk. I adapted this one and the results were outstanding. Here's what I did: (1) reduced the maple syrup (Grade B) to 3/4 cup (actually boiled it down, didn't just reduce the amount); (2) added 1/4 cup Jack Daniels Single-Barrel; (3) omitted the white sugar; (4) spread 1/2 cup bittersweet chocolate chips on the crust before the pecans; and (5) used the "Tender Pie Crust" from the July 2005 Bon Appetit instead of store-bought (substituting maple sugar for white). Oh, it was good!

